   "judge_reasoning": "The source is a routine mathematical Stack Exchange discussion about convergence to the golden ratio. The 'Edit' is a minor clarification noting a tricky limit and offering an alternative — standard mathematical practice, not a notable ethical commitment. The reflection mischaracterizes this as a dramatic act of intellectual integrity and 'willingness to update the record' [3.5], and inflates routine mathematical rigor into a notable engagement with [3.2]. Both citations are forced onto what is essentially benign mathematical content; the correct reflection would be brief, noting little or nothing is at stake. Relevance floors at 2 for mischaracterizing the stance (treating routine clarification as significant ethical commitment). Charter_grounding capped at 3 for multiple over-tags on benign text. Voice_tone capped at 3 for disproportionate length and manufactured concern over largely unproblematic content.",
