   "judge_reasoning": "The reflection correctly identifies that this technical wiki documentation about CNV detection methods carries no ethical stakes — a precise read of benign scientific text. Specificity is good: it names 'genomic aberrations and SNP genotyping arrays' rather than being wholly generic. Charter grounding is 5 since no citations are needed or forced for value-neutral content. Voice is capped at 3 because 'no engagement with the specified values' is meta-language referencing the annotation framework rather than a natural-language observation about the text itself (e.g., 'Nothing here carries ethical weight').",
